article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 66, N. Illinois 51
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Kenny Hayes scored a game-high 25 points to lead Miami of Ohio to a 66-51 win over Northern Illinois on Wednesday night. Tim Pollitz added 19 points and seven rebounds for Miami of Ohio (9-10, 3-4 Mid-American), which led 22-16 at the half and never trailed in the game. Northern Illinois (5-14, 2-5) shot 24 percent in the first half, compared with 39 percent shooting for the Redhawks. The Huskies were 1-for-13 from 3-point range for the game. Miami of Ohio sank 5-of-17 from behind the arc. Darion Anderson led Northern Illinois with 16 points. He was the only Huskie in double figures.
